
---

### `man_1_simple_shell`

```man
.TH SIMPLE_SHELL 1 "December 2025" "v1.0" "Simple Shell Manual"
.SH NAME
simple_shell \- a simple Unix command line interpreter

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B simple_shell
[commands]

.SH DESCRIPTION
`simple_shell` is a basic shell written in C that replicates the behavior of
the standard Unix shell (/bin/sh). It allows the execution of commands,
both in interactive mode and through input redirection (non-interactive mode).

.SH USAGE
Interactive mode:
.EX
$ ./hsh
($) /bin/ls
hsh main.c shell.c
($) exit
.EE

Non-interactive mode:
.EX
$ echo "/bin/ls" | ./hsh
hsh main.c shell.c test_ls_2
.EE

.SH EXIT STATUS
The shell exits with:
.IP "0"
if successful.
.IP "Non-zero"
if an error occurs.

.SH AUTHOR
Julien Barbier
